$ cd /media/sda3/home/nxd/test/
$ tar xvzf qscript-0.11.tar.gz

Building qscript requires the following directory structure where qscript-0.11
is the top level directory:

The directory structure is already in the tarball, but documented here
in case something goes wrong

/media/sda3/home/nxd/test/qscript-0.11
|-- bin
|-- cmake
|   `-- modules
|-- config
|-- include
|-- inputs
|-- lib
|-- make-build-dir
|   |-- compiletime_lib
|   |-- compiletime_static_lib
|   |-- runtime_lib
|   `-- runtime_static_lib
|-- resources
|-- src
`-- testsuite
    |-- config
    `-- qscript.test


The following command will build the compiler, but you need the following 
1. ncurses (with the development header files and library)
2. g++


1. Command to build the compiler

	qscript-0.11$ make -f CustomQScriptMakefile local_install

2. Ensure that the bin directory contains "qscript"

3. Test the compiler
	qscript-0.11$ export QSCRIPT_HOME=`pwd`
	qscript-0.11$ cd inputs
	qscript-0.11/inputs$ ../bin/qscript -n -f inp_jump_test

	compiler should generate inp_jump_test.C, inp_jump_test.exe

4.	Execute the generated file
	qscript-0.11/inputs$ LD_LIBARARY_PATH=$QSCRIPT_HOME/lib inp_jump_test.exe

